If you accidentally submitted your project to the wrong assignment, why can't you just show this to your instructors, they can check the time stamp, and you get your points back? Did you submit someone else's assignment and that's why you're freaking out?

history.content: I think it is better for you to speak with the instructors and see if they can resolve the issue (I'm sure it can be done and I'm confident weaver would be willing to make this consideration especially since it was done in error even after you did the work).

I'm currently also taking another CS upper div and 2 stat upper divs (both of which fulfill the technical elective requirement according to the EECS website, I think).
